Class:
     It is blue print or Template 
Object:
     An instance of the class is called Object
     
.java
     import : java.lang.*;
     Extends : java.lang.Object
 
 What is constructor ?
  - Special method, whose name same as class name
  - There is no return type (void also shouldn't written)
  - It can't be called explicitly, it is called by the JVM by using new keyword
  - It is called only once for the Object
  - If there no user defined constructor in the class then java compiler provides default constructor
  - Class can any number constructors with different param list, this is called constructor overloading 
  
  
  this: used to call instance variable from the local scope.
  this(): used to call constructor of the same class with different param list from another constructor
  
  Overloading:
   1. No of params
   2. Order of params
   3. Types of params 
   
  
  IIB
  Static
  
  Interface
  Abstract class
  
  
  
  
  
  overriding:
   1. Can't reduce visibility, it should same or less restrictive access specifier  
  
